FBIS4-57739 "drlat100_i_94006" FBIS-LAT-94-100 Daily Report 23 May 1994 Nicaragua Commander Tomas Borge Closes FSLN Special Congress Commander Tomas Borge Closes FSLN Special Congress PA2305232694 Managua Radio Sandino in Spanish 1513 GMT 23 May 94 PA2305232694 Managua Radio Sandino Spanish BFN [Statement by Commander Tomas Borge to close the Sandinist National Liberation Front, FSLN, Special Congress at the Olof Palme Convention Center in Managua -- live] [Text] [Words indistinct] shown by you during 76 hours of nearly uninterrupted work, with the efforts of support teams -- which have carried out their work unselfishly -- with the efforts of the Electoral Council -- which has worked virtually without rest just as we did -- [and with the efforts] of the entire personnel, the physicians, and others who helped us ensure that this Congress worked, and with the extreme discipline, mutual respect, and the joy that was present in this event. I do not know how to reward you other than by expressing our affection, but perhaps the biggest reward that we could give you after these 76 hours, is to be brief now. Thus, I declare the FSLN Special Congress closed. [applause]
